  "title": "Marketing Assistant Manager",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a creative Marketing Manager to lead the promotion of our upcoming shows and live events. <br />You will be responsible for driving stand-up comedy ticket sales, and planning fun events for local audiences. <br />You need to be interested in comedy shows or have similar experiences.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>• Campaign Strategy: Design and execute 360° marketing plans from announcement to show day.<br />• Digital Growth: Manage social media, email marketing, and paid ad spend (Meta, TikTok, Google) to maximize ROI.<br />• Partnerships: Coordinate with ticketing platforms (e.g., SISTIC, Ticketmaster), media partners, and influencers.<br />• Content Creation: Oversee the production of high-quality visuals and copy that resonate with fanbases.<br />• On-site Support: Manage media and capture content during live shows.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>• experience in marketing (Music, Entertainment, or Agency background preferred).<br />• Speck& write in Chinese!!!<br />• Fan-First Mindset: Deep understanding of current music trends and fan culture.<br />• Agility: Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, high-pressure environment.</p>",
